---

## POST /users

### Description

Creates a new user account in the system. The endpoint accepts user details in the request body and returns the newly created user object along with a unique identifier.

- **URL:** `/users`
- **Method:** `POST`
- **Auth Required:** Yes (`Bearer` token)
- **Content-Type:** `application/json`

---

### Request

#### Headers

| Header          | Value              | Required |
|-----------------|--------------------|----------|
| Authorization   | Bearer `<token>`   | Yes      |
| Content-Type    | application/json   | Yes      |

#### Body Parameters

| Field      | Type   | Required | Description                          |
|------------|--------|----------|--------------------------------------|
| name       | string | Yes      | Full name of the user (1–100 chars)  |
| email      | string | Yes      | A valid, unique email address        |
| password   | string | Yes      | Password (min 8 characters)          |
| role       | string | No       | User role (`admin` or `member`). Defaults to `member` |

#### Example Request

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.example.com/users \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR..." \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
    "password": "s3cur3P@ss!",
    "role": "member"
  }'
```

---

### Response

#### Success Response — `201 Created`

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
    "role": "member",
    "createdAt": "2025-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

#### Error Responses

**`400 Bad Request`** — Validation failed

```json
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "errors": [
    { "field": "email", "message": "A valid email address is required." },
    { "field": "password", "message": "Password must be at least 8 characters." }
  ]
}
```

**`409 Conflict`** — Email already exists

```json
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "A user with this email address already exists."
}
```

**`401 Unauthorized`** — Missing or invalid token

```json
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Authentication token is missing or invalid."
}
```

---

### Notes

- Passwords are hashed before storage and are **never** returned in responses.
- The `id` field is a system-generated UUID.
- The `createdAt` timestamp is in ISO 8601 format (UTC).
